com.kuka.objectparameters

Interface IBasicParameterMap

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IObjectParameter, IParameterComposite
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IParameterMap, IParameterStructure, ITypedParameterMap

    public interface IBasicParameterMap
extends IParameterComposite
    An object parameter that contains other object parameters identified by their names.

    The name of each object parameter is used as key. This map represents a mapping of object parameter name to object parameter instance.

    • Method Detail

      • get

        IObjectParameter get(String key)
        Gets the object parameter associated with the specified key in this parameter map.

        The object parameter name serves as key, so this method gets the object parameter with the specified name. If no such parameter is contained in this parameter map, null is returned.

        Parameters:
        key - the name of the parameter to get
        Returns:
        the object parameter associated with the specified key, or null, if no such parameter is contained in this parameter map

      • get

        <T extends IObjectParameter> T get(String key,
                                   Class<T> clazz)
        Gets the object parameter associated with the specified key and the specified type contained in this parameter map.

        The object parameter name serves as key, so this method gets the object parameter with the specified name and the specified type. If no such parameter is contained in this parameter map, null is returned.

        Type Parameters:
        T - Object extending the interface IObjectParameter
        Parameters:
        key - the name of the parameter to get
        clazz - the type of the parameter to get
        Returns:
        the object parameter of the specified type associated with the specified key, or null, if no such parameter is contained in this parameter map
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the object parameter associated with the specified key is not of the specified type

      • containsKey

        boolean containsKey(String key)
        Returns true if this map contains a mapping for the specified key. More formally, returns true if and only if this map contains a mapping for a key k such that (key==null ? k==null : key.equals(k)). (There can be at most one such mapping.)

        The object parameter name serves as key, so this method returns true, if this map contains an object parameter with the specified name

        Parameters:
        key - parameter name whose existence in this map is to be tested
        Returns:
        true if this map contains a mapping for the specified parameter name

      • size

        int size()
        Returns the number of key-value mappings in this map. If the map contains more than Integer.MAX_VALUE elements, returns Integer.MAX_VALUE.
        Returns:
        the number of key-value mappings in this map
